rComments: This was easily the best course I have ever taken. There was a ton of reading and the subject matter was heavy to say the least, but I came out with a much deeper respect for literature and much higher aspirations for my academic career. I expected British literature to be a bunch of old white men and this was thoroughly rejected in an awesome way!

His lectures can be a little dry, but you can tell that he really cares about his students. He has always emailed me back within twenty minutes of contacting him, even at 10 pm, and he's extremely helpful and understanding. Not a prof you have to be scared of, though perhaps a little boring if you aren't super interested in the class topic.

If you enjoy talking about a 7 line poem for 3 hours this is your class.  I did not think it was possible to take the fun out of poetry and drama but boy oh boy did this prof do just that. On the plus side Mondays were the only night i went to bed before 10:30 because the class put me right to sleep. 0/10 do not take this prof

rComments: Great professor. You could see he put a lot of effort into his teaching and his powerpoint slides were very clear. Class discussion was fascinating. He gives excellent constructive criticism and encouragement on assignments and he's very nice to students. I enjoy and appreciate poetry so much more after this course.
